This paper is likely to belong to the Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) sub-category as it deals with the discovery of morphologically related words in an unannotated corpus. It also uses semantic similarity measures, which are commonly used in natural language processing tasks. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. 

Information Retrieval (cs.IR) is another possible sub-category as the algorithm involves ranking probable morphologically related pairs. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is also a possible sub-category as the paper involves developing an algorithm that can discover patterns in unannotated data. 

Finally, Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves developing an algorithm that can efficiently find morphologically related pairs in a large corpus.
